      "instructions": "Procedures                                                                              1                                                                            Place chicken, ginger, and wine in a medium saucepan. Add enough cold water to barely cover chicken. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat then reduce to lowest heat. Liquid should be barely quivering. Cook until chicken is cooked through (breasts should register 155°F on an instant read thermometer and legs should register at least 165°F).                                                                                                                            2                                                                            Remove chicken from the pot and place into a bowl of ice water. Leave it to cool in the water, up to 2 hours, or remove and place it in the refrigerator for longer storage.  When are you ready to dress the chicken, tear the meat into slivers.                                                                                                                            3                                                                            Combine sugar, salt, soy sauce, vinegar, sesame paste, sesame oil, chili oil, and sichuan peppercorns in a medium mixing bowl. Whisk to combine. Add chicken, scallions, cilantro, sesame seeds, and peanuts. Toss to combine and season to taste with additional chili oil, vinegar, or soy sauce as desired. Serve immediately, or refrigerate for up to 2 days.",
