      "instructions": "In a large soup pot, heat the oil and garlic over medium-high heat until the garlic begins to sizzle. Add the chili powder, cumin and stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds.Add the creamed corn, diced tomatoes, chicken broth, black beans, chiles, and chicken and stir to combine. Bring the mixture to a boil, reduce the heat to low and simmer, partially covered, to blend the flavors, about 5 minutes.Stir in the cilantro and season to taste with salt and pepper",
