      "instructions": "Heat the olive oil over medium heat in large pot or Dutch oven. Add the turkey sausage, breaking up with wooden spoon, stirring occasionally until cooked through, about 5 minutes. Remove from the pan with a slotted spoon and place in a bowl. Set aside.Add the red onion to the pan, cooking until softened, about 5 minutes, adding more oil if the pan becomes dry. Add the garlic, bell peppers, and jalapeos, and saut for 2 minutes or until slightly softened. Add the butternut squash and spices, and saut for 1 minute. Stir in the tomato paste, then add 1 cups of the chicken stock. Mix the remaining  cup chicken stock in a bowl with half of the beans, and mash. Stir this into the pot and bring the liquid to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer on low heat until the butternut squash is tender, about 10 minutes. Add the turkey sausage and remaining beans, and simmer another 10- 15 minutes more. Remove from heat and stir in the chopped cilantro and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and enjoy!",
